[40:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'free for you to use via this platform. So, if you\'re interested, I\'ll link to this page in the description below. Next up, this AI by Google DeepMind is also very interesting. So, it\'s called Fizz'

[40:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'World. And this is essentially a system that helps robots learn how to do certain actions just by watching videos. So, it works like this. All you need to do is give it an image and an action.'

[40:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'And the system would first create a video using Google\'s VO showing the action being done. Now, you can\'t just feed this video to a robot and just hope that it can copy the motions. And that\'s'

[40:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'because it could ignore some real world physics. So the next step is this system actually plugs this video into a tool called realto sim which basically reconstructs this action in a 3D'

[40:54] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'simulation and within the simulation it follows all the laws of physics. It makes sure that everything is physically correct. And then the robot is basically trained in this virtual simulation for'

[41:06] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'like thousands of iterations. And then afterwards, if you deploy this in the real world, as you can see, the robot is actually able to do this action very well. Here are some other examples for'

[41:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'your reference. So in summary, this is basically a system where we no longer actually need to train robots using real physical data. We can just generate videos using V3 or any other video model'

[41:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'and then plug it through this realtosim virtual world and then train the robot there. And from that these robots are able to learn tasks that they have never seen before. Now the strength of this'

[41:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'approach is that we don\'t actually need to collect or record any physical data. Everything generated including the training data including the simulations are synthetic. It\'s all generated with'

[41:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'AI. And this of course makes it way more efficient and cheap compared to actually training a robot physically in the real world. The nice thing is if you scroll up to the top of the page, they\'ve released the code to this. So if you'

[42:08] [scene:talk]
